## Bugs

- **Basis/Hamiltonian/Structure mismatch → domain exceptions:** BSpline+DFT/DHF (no evaluator), SG(atom-only)
  for a Molecule, LibCint+DFT (no 3-centre). These currently throw `bad_cast`; catch + re-throw a
  `BasisSetSupport` exception carrying basis type + required/missing support (RKB/DFT). Clients: `DiracKinetic`,
  `FittedVee`. (Ties to the CLAUDE.md `dynamic_cast` survey.)  I am purposly leaving aspect un-implemented ths is a static test of the mix architecture.
- IntegralsCache RAM report messy only for BSpline (RadialType dumps the grid). RESOLVED-as-non-bug:
  SG/SL coarse RadialType()==Name() is SAFE — the ExponentGrouper keys each distinct exponent VALUE to its
  own index (integral uses grouper.unique_esv[i]); guarded now by Cache4Tests.HF2_S{G,L}_ExponentKeyed.
  BSpline is the ODD one out: its grouper keys splines by rmin ONLY (Grouper.C: "assume same rmin => same
  rmax"), so it genuinely needs the full grid in RadialType to keep grids in separate caches -> messy report.
  Real cleanup (low prio): give BSpline a proper grid-fingerprint grouper, then it too could use a coarse
  RadialType and the report would be clean. NOT a correctness issue.

## OOD principles & north-star

- Capital "SOLID" = OOD principles; lowercase "solid" = periodic-lattice materials.
- Ultimate target: VASP/ABINIT-class (ultrasoft) pseudopotentials. HF/DHF support follows purely from whether
  the Evaluator satisfies the integral concepts.
- **Priorities (in order):** (1) correct numbers, (2) efficient (CPU/RAM), (3) easy end-user interface,
  (4) easy developer interface for adding basis-set/pseudopotential types ← where the pseudo-wall matters,
  (5) readable (code looks like the literature formula, e.g. `sqrt(α+β)`). The wall is not perfection: the
  basis interface should *stabilize* after a few pseudopotential types, then the rest are a breeze.
- **Why physical total energies matter (north-star):** voltage curves for Li/Na battery materials
  (LiMn2O4, LiNiO2, LiCoO2): (1) TEs for different Li configs (often supercells); (2) interaction strengths
  for a lattice-gas (Ising 0/1); (3) Monte-Carlo → V(T,x). Implies multi-species PP (done), spin+U, forces.
- **The big abstraction question:** correct abstractions for a clean
  `{atom/molecule/Lattice_3D/2D/1D} × {1E,DFT,HF} × {Pol,unPol}`. see the "The three axes" section in NOTES

## Questions

- Atoms often use a numerical radial-DE solution instead of basis sets. Fit into the framework? Treat the
  radial solution as a 1-function IBS; an alternate `UpdateOrbitals` (`Orbitals/.../TOrbitals.C`) does a
  numerical radial solve per irrep from the current density. (Many hard details elided.)

