## Solids / plane waves

- **APW energy-dependent overlap** (`APW_IBS` is an `IrrepBasisSet<dcmplx>` but deliberately not an
  `Orbital_1E_IBS`): solve the nonlinear secular eq by iterating — guess E₀, build H(E₀),O(E₀); solve the
  generalized problem → ε_n(E₀); set E₀←E₁ until fixed point. Like an SCF except we find E* (not a density)
  and S(E) also changes each iteration.
  Need to see wat real SCF looks like on APW with DFT. 
- **Mid-level plan:** (1) go far along lineage A & B; (2) lineage A: `template<isM_1E_Evaluator E> class
  EPlaneWave_IBS<E>`, migrate the hardcoded PW IBSs one at a time (most data → evaluators); (3) graft onto
  lineage B; (4) e-e repulsion (needs the DFT upgrade first). Also: GPW/GAPW after FLAPW — we have Gaussian
  integral engines in `src/BasisSet/Molecule` if that helps.

- Submodule tiny-diffs (blaze, wignerSymbols, libxc): CMake min-version noise + blaze compiler warnings.
  libxc xc.h mtime churn is patched (write-only-if-changed). Better long-term handling? (keep a patch,
  re-apply after checkout?)


# By library or project-module

## qcHamiltonian

- **bare->r\* rename** (remove transitional aliases): bare names (`Static_HT`, `Dynamic_HT`,
  `Hamiltonian`, `Static_CC`, `Dynamic_CC`, `DM_CD`, `Composite_CD`, `obs_t`, ...) are still
  `using X = rX` shims so ~200 existing sites didn't churn. Do the codebase-wide rename. NOTE the
  `rHamiltonian` rename must also dissolve the `qchem::Hamiltonian` namespace-vs-type shadow
  (the `::Hamiltonian` / `qchem::Hamiltonian::` qualifications scattered around are working around it).
- We need a graceful way to make a DFT Hamiltonian from a purely numeric (superposition of atoms) charge density.  Right now we have the misnamed CompositeFittedCD which serves this purpose, but it inherets the  tChargeDensity interface and then stubs out the function that it obviously has no (efficient) way of implementing: GetRepulsion3C. We need to 1) rename CompositeFittedCD->NumericCD 2) Allow a second construction channel for DFT Hamiltonians that accepts a ScalarFunction<double>, that is all it need to fit Vee and Vxc.  2) Make sure HF and DHF Hamiltonians do not have the alternate constructor.

### Friendly libxc interface
- Clients shouldn't have to look up a function id. Pick a few popular/common functionals we want, make enums,
  handle params for the user — hide that libxc is under the hood.

## qcChargeDensity
**Charge density / SCF**
- Seeding mechanism: not user-friendly (uniform-density-seed boilerplate in the framework tests), and crude
  for ionic charge-transfer (NaF/CsI converge but grind).  see doc/SCFSeedingPlan.md
- Harden versioning
```c++
    virtual bool   isActive() const = 0;   // Layer 2: am I the live head of my lineage?
```
  Then the consuming side asserts the invariant:
```c++
    const hmat_t& GetMatrix(..., const tDM_CD* cd) const
    {
        assert(cd->isActive() && "computing with a superseded charge density");
        ...
    }
```
  So if anyone hands the Hamiltonian a density that's been superseded, it fires immediately — pointing at the exact line, instead of producing a plausible-but-wrong number.

## qcFitting

**Small follow-ups from this session's cleanups**
- `FIT_CD_ABS<T>` / `FIT_SF_ABS<T>` templating — left non-templated; the `<dcmplx>` vision is still open.
- `FourierFunctionFitter` delete-and-inline — kept the named object; the aggressive alternative remains.
- XC energy `∫ε_xc·ρ` through the fitter — still on the direct grid route (needs a grid-based fit input).

## qcAtom_BS
- **Dirac/RKB:** 1s orbital not properly normalized; track kinetic factors (0.5, c, 2c).
- **Dirac/RKB:** `Orbital_DHF_IBS.C::merge_xxx`: use `blazem::submatrix`.
- **Atom evaluators:** Gaussian integrals via recursion `Fact[n]/pow(2,n)` (consider `constexpr`); convert
  the BSpline Fortran GL integrator (`Atom/Evaluators/BSpline/Internal/gauleg.f`) to C++/blaze and fold into
  qcMesh — BSpline and PW should share one 1-D GL.
- `op()(rvec3_t)` is the universal evaluation interface (full angular dependence, real Ylm — the future GUI
  needs honest truth). Atom DFT integration should exploit spherical symmetry analytically (1-D radial × 4π),
  NOT fake a 3-D grid down one axis. Make integration a polymorphic quadrature strategy chosen by the basis's
  symmetry (atom carries YFactory). **Principle to lock now:** `op(rvec3_t)` is always honest; a fast
  `op(double r)` may exist only as the radial integrator's internal fast-path, never a public alternative.
  Defer to GUI time, but don't let the deferral accrete a flag.
- **Lossless BSpline grouper** (so `RadialType()` can drop to bare `Name()` like SG/SL, fixing the messy
  IntegralsCache RAM report — see the Bugs note). Root cause: the spline `ExponentGrouper` keys splines by
  `rmin` ONLY (Grouper.C: "assume same rmin => same rmax") — lossy for splines — so BSpline currently smuggles
  the whole grid into `RadialType()` to keep distinct grids in distinct caches. Fix: give the spline grouper a
  TRUE lossless key for a spline's identity (full knot-vector / grid fingerprint, not just rmin), so two grids
  never alias even under a coarse `"BSpline<K>"` RadialType; then `RadialType()` returns just `Name()` and the
  report is clean. Mirror the SG/SL guard: add a two-distinct-grid analogue of
  `Cache4Tests.HF2_S{G,L}_ExponentKeyed` (different grids -> distinct integrals, fnorm>0).
- BSpline Rk routines should use cached values for all splines at all GL grid points.  find() inside BSpline(r) is is 90% of the cpu

