## qcLattice_3D
**Pinned design reviews**
- Scalars leaking through abstract interfaces: `ExternalG0Energy` (PW-specific, no molecular-ECP analogue)
  and the `double& Eh` out-param on `Repulsion(const FourierMap&, double&)`.
- `BasisSet<dcmplx>::Create{CD,Vxc}FitBasisSet` NA-stubs (`src/BasisSet/Imp/BasisSet.C`) — the "dirty code
  smell" to revisit ("PW reuses its own basis for fitting" ≠ "those fakes are fine").
- BZ-symmetry reduction — multi-k computes all k-points explicitly; fold to the irreducible wedge (+weights) using the crystal point group when k-counts grow. (Perf, not correctness.)
## qcPseudoPotential

**Pseudopotential / multi-species**
- `Qli`   , so heavy semicore valences (e.g. Cs **q9**)
  aren't usable; sidestepped with Cs q1. Small self-contained addition.

## qcElConfig
- Can we make an EC_Aufbau that does aufbau filling across irreps for atom/molecule and solids? Or does each
  structure type have its own peculiarities?

## qcSymmetry

- **Space-group support** — extend qcSymmetry from molecular point groups + Bloch k-labels to crystal space
  groups. Three sub-tasks: (1) **detect** the ops from cell+basis (spglib-style); (2) **represent** `{R|τ}`
  and apply them (to k in reciprocal space; to positions/density in real space); (3) **BZ machinery** — star
  of k, irreducible wedge, integration weights.
  - **Tier A** — point group acting on k (+ time-reversal `k→−k`). Enough for BZ reduction (consumes only the
    point-group part; symmorphic-friendly). This is the provider for the qcLattice_3D *BZ-symmetry reduction*
    item.
  - **Tier B** — full space group with fractional translations τ → non-symmorphic `e^{−iG·τ}` phases,
    density/Hamiltonian symmetrization, crystal SALCs (solid analogue of the molecular SALC work).
  - Reuses the molecular point-group core: a space group ≈ point group ⋉ lattice translations.

